definitions.definition: An Aegean island chain in southeast-central Greece , surrounding the main island Delos , further including the islands of Andros , Amorgos , Irakleia , Kea , Mykonos Naxos , Paros , Santorini , Syra , Tinos and others.

main_definition: An Aegean island chain in southeast-central Greece , surrounding the main island Delos , further including the islands of Andros , Amorgos , Irakleia , Kea , Mykonos Naxos , Paros , Santorini , Syra , Tinos and others.
